<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">What Happens if I Add the Wrong Amount of Ba=
king Powder?</h2>



<p>Using the wrong amount of baking powder in a recipe like this <a href=3D=
"https://simple-veganista.com/vegan-banana-tea-bread/">Vegan Banana Bread</=
a> or <a href=3D"https://simple-veganista.com/vegan-blueberry-muffins/">Blu=
eberry Muffins</a> can have a number of effects on the end results of your =
baked goods. If you use too much baking powder, it may be too light and air=
y from rising too much and have a slightly bitter taste. If you use too lit=
tle baking powder, it may turn out to be dense and heavy and not rise prope=
rly. A general rule is to use between 1 to 1 1/4 teaspoons (tsp) of baking =
powder per 1 cup of flour. </p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_6_tablet" class=
=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content adthrive-content-6 adthrive-ad-cls" style=
=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Can I Use Tableware as Measuring Spoons?</h2=
>



<p>There was a time when it was common to use small and large silverware sp=
oons to measure ingredients. Today, measuring spoons are standardized, whil=
e silverware sizes can vary. For this reason, it=E2=80=99s not recommended =
to use silverware to measure ingredients for recipes. But when in a pinch, =
and you don=E2=80=99t have a standard measuring tsp or tbsp, you can use a =
small silverware spoon to measure a teaspoon or a larger spoon to use as a =
tablespoon.</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">How Much is a Pinch or Dash?</h2>



<p>Before standardized measuring tools, cooks often used their hands, finge=
rs, or common household items to measure ingredients, leading to the use of=
 terms like =E2=80=9Cpinch=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cdash.=E2=80=9D Even still =
today, a recipe will call for a pinch, dash, or smidgen of an ingredient. I=
n general, these terms all mean the same thing.</p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Pinch:</strong> About 1/8 of a teaspoon (tsp) of a dry ingredie=
nt, such as salt, pepper, or spices. Usually, just enough to fit between th=
e forefinger and thumb.</li>



<li><strong>Dash: </strong>Refers to adding a tiny amount of a dry or wet i=
ngredient. A dash is generally less than half of 1/8 teaspoon (tsp).</li>
</ul>



<p class=3D"has-background" style=3D"background-color:#f7f7f7">See more kit=
chen references: <a href=3D"https://simple-veganista.com/cooking-terms/">Co=
oking Terms + Definitions A =E2=80=93 Z</a></p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">FAQ=E2=80=99s</h2>



<p><strong>How many 1/2 teaspoons (tsp) are in 1 tablespoon (tbsp)?</strong=
><br>There are 6 half (1/2) teaspoons in 1 tablespoon in the US Customary S=
ystem. This conversion is true since there are 2 half (1/2) teaspoons in 1 =
teaspoon and 3 teaspoons in 1 tablespoon. So multiply the 2 half (1/2) tsp =
by 3 tsp =3D 6 half (1/2) tsp in a tbsp.</p>



<p><strong>How many 1/4 teaspoons are in a tablespoon?</strong><br>There ar=
e 12 =E2=80=93 1/4 teaspoons in 1 tablespoon in the US Customary System. Th=
is conversion is true since there are 4 (1/4) teaspoons in 1 teaspoon and 3=
 teaspoons in 1 tablespoon. We multiply the 4 =E2=80=93 1/4 teaspoons by 3 =
teaspoons which is 12 (1/4) tsp in a tbsp.</p>



<p><strong>How many teaspoons are in a UK tablespoon?</strong><br>There are=
 4 teaspoons in 1 UK tablespoon.</p>



<p><strong>How many teaspoons are in an Australian tablespoon (AUS)?</stron=
g><br>There are 4 teaspoons in a tablespoon in Australia. This conversion i=
s true because 1 Australian teaspoon is equal to 5 milliliters, and 1 Austr=
alian tablespoon equals 20 milliliters. Simply divide 20ml (Aus Tbsp) by 5 =
milliliters (1 AUS tsp) which equals 4 teaspoons.</p>



<p><strong>How many tablespoons are in a stick of butter?</strong><br>In th=
e US, a stick of butter typically weighs 4 ounces (113 grams) and contains =
8 tablespoons. This is equivalent to 1/2 cup or 1/4 pound of butter.</p><di=
v id=3D"AdThrive_Content_7_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content ad=
thrive-content-7 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>



<p><strong>How many tablespoons in an ounce?</strong><br>In the United Stat=
es, there are 2 tablespoons in 1 fluid ounce.</p>



<p class=3D"has-background" style=3D"background-color:#f7f7f7">I hope this =
conversion guide has been helpful and you learned something new about the e=
ver-so-handy and humble teaspoon and tablespoon! </p>



